Text.Value: |*Calm raven down with your im-peck-able animal handling techniques*|
|Well, okay, most of the time I just scavenge the area.|
|No, they're mine. No touchy.|
|I explicitly told you to leave and I'm not interested in what you have to say|
|Oh, I'm sorry, I did't realize. I'll take my leave now.|
|Yeah. But I still live here. And you're invading on my living space|
|Oh, hello again|
|Bye and don't come any closer|
|Ka-kaw!|
|Ka-kaw!|
|Your jokes suck and so do you. Leave my home now|
|Oh, you noticed! Yeah, it was quite a hassle to get them!|
|*Just prepare to fight raven for no good reason*|
|Ha! Those are some nice jokes!|
|Actually, I just wanted your feedback on my stand up routine? It goes something like that...|
|So, what do you do here?|
|This literally is just a rooftop though? I just stumbled into you|
|Ca-caw!|
|Th.. The audacity!|
|Tsk! What else did I expect|
|Uh, live?|
|Lately there has been an influx of those cultists - provide quite a nice food source. Not much else to say|
|*Hard to say whether raven was impressed by your skillcheck or a pun, but it isn't threatened by you anymore*|
|*The raven is unnerved by your presence and clearly wants you to leave*|
|*Raven is calmed down and unconcerned with you being around*|
|*Slowly back off *|
|Can I have those very cool ingredients?|
|H... Hi? What are you doing at my home?|
|Didn't I tell you to leave?|
|*That didn't work and raven seems upset and agressive now*|
|*Notice all the cool stuff raven gathered and complinet its scavenging squills*|
|*Raven is still concerned but not hostile*|
|Bye|
|Those are MINE! Don't come any closer to them!|
|Ca-Caw!|
|*Take your leave*|
|We haven't talked yet, but your friends seem nice enough to let you hang around|
|Okay, I'll take my leave|
|Sure, you do seem like a nice enough person. Consider yourself my guest, but nothing more|
|I'm not gonna take orders from a harpy *attack*|
|I'm not gonna take orders from a harpy *attack*|
|About time|
|Oh, I see there are some cool ingredients you have lying around? I'd really like to discuss those!|
